13. Google Earth export

I don’t think anyone but me actually uses my Google Earth export these days, but it’s cool.

Running “actium.pl stops2kmz whatever.kmz” will output a Google Earth .kmz file with custom placemarks for each stop, that have the stop ID in the image. It uses the data from the FileMaker database.

The placemark has the stop ID and the text has the lines that serve each stop. Different colors represent stops that have only school lines, stops with Transbay lines, Tempo stops, etc. Black are inactive stops. The small shape indicates what kind of at-stop sign is present, if any.

The placemarks are stored in PubInfSys – Documents/Actium/signups/common/kmlicons.zip. The source for them (the Illustrator files and the script that made them) is in /PubInfSys - Documents/Online Projects/Google Earth export
